The '''16th Dallas-Fort Worth Film Critics Association Awards''', given by the [[Dallas-Fort Worth Film Critics Association]] on December 16, 2009, honored the best in film for [[2009 in film|2009]].
==Winners and runners-up== Winners are listed first and highlighted with '''boldface'''. Other films ranked by the annual poll are listed in order. While most categories saw 5 honorees named, some categories ranged from as many as 10 (Best Film) to as few as 2 (Best Cinematography, Best Animated Film, Best Screenplay).
